<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WOMAN FOUND FATALLY SHOT ON PAXTON AVENUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department is investigating the death of an 
unidentified woman who was found shot to death Wednesday on a street in the 
Lopez Canyon area, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
A passing Los Angeles police officer found the body of the adult woman at 3:36 
a.m. in the 12300 block of Paxton Avenue, Sheriff's Sgt. Bryan Williams said. 
That part of Paxton, in a small area of unincorporated county territory between 
Lake View Terrace and Pacoima, is routinely used by Los Angeles police officers 
driving between the two neighborhoods. 
</P>
<P>
Williams said detectives have not determined a motive for the shooting and have 
no suspects. 
</P>
