YOU CAN HELP!: ASSISTANCE FOR HER BEST SERVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HERB HAIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lenore Handy of Fullerton has her eye out for another fiberglass serving tray 
with Hawaiian design (flowers, leaves, ferns) that used to come in many colors 
and measured about 8x14 inches. Can you come up with a source that will serve 
Handy right, or will she either have to lei off giving luaus or just tray a 
littler harder? 
</P>
<P>
H. G. Wolfe of Glendale is looking for some 20-inch wooden coat hangers sold 
under the Setwell label; they are the only type on which her coats hang 
properly, but she can't find them. Can you help pin something on Wolfe, or will 
her coats always have that hung-over look? 
</P>
<P>
Ruth E. Jimenez of Whittier needs some aluminum-frame patio chairs that have 
redwood slats instead of plastic webbing. Can you help put Jimenez's back-yard 
furniture on a firm basis, or will she have to wonder whether her future as an 
outdoor entertainer is already behind her? 
</P>
<P>
Reader-to-Reader Help Line: Sally at (818) 286-9434 is looking for a galvanized 
one-gallon watering can no longer available in the stores; it is 6 inches high 
(not counting the handle), 8 1/2 inches long and 6 inches wide; the spout is 
about 8 inches long. Please don't pour any more cold water than necessary on 
Sally's already not-so-high hopes. . . . Lyla at (714) 855-1777 would like to 
get hold of a Dressy Bessie doll; she claims it's great for kindergarten 
children to practice buttoning and zippering. Please help add some zip to her 
youngsters' education and improve their button-down minds. . . . Robert at 
(818) 545-8579 wants to get his hands on an old-fashioned wooden top that is 
activated by a string wound around it. Please get to the bottom of this and put 
Robert on top of the world. . . . Ann at (213) 465-9685 needs an out-of-print 
astrology book called "Sun Sign Revelations." It was written by a woman -- not 
Linda Goodman -- with a Spanish surname. Please show Ann a small sign of 
progress before she begins to see stars in front of her eyes. 
</P>
<P>
Note: The Reader-to-Reader Help Line is only for one-time items or for products 
no longer available in stores. And you must give us written permission to 
publish your telephone number, so that others may contact you directly. 
</P>
<P>
Hain cannot answer mail personally but will, space permitting, respond in this 
column to readers who need -- or have -- helpful information. Write (do not 
telephone) to You Can Help!, You section, the Times, Times Mirror Square, Los 
Angeles 90053. 
