<TEXT>
<P>
Although there are several holidays between now and then, Hallmark Cards has 
already booked the pre-Valentine's Day show for its "Hallmark Hall of Fame" on 
CBS. It will be "Face to Face," a romantic drama starring Elizabeth Montgomery 
and Robert Foxworth as two strong-willed people who fall in love in spite of 
themselves. The film was shot on location in Kenya. A Hallmark executive notes 
that the slot is important for the company because Valentine's Day is the 
second most popular greeting-card occasion of the year, behind Christmas. 
ALEENE MacMINN 
