<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: WHITTIER; 
</P>
<P>
UPTOWN GYM OWNERS PLEAD INNOCENT TO DRUG CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Owners of the Uptown Gym in Whittier pleaded innocent Tuesday to charges of 
possessing anabolic steroids and cocaine for sale. 
</P>
<P>
Richard C. Gill, 49, and Rick Weaver, 45, had been charged in Whittier 
Municipal Court with one count each of possession of cocaine for sale, 
possession of anabolic steroids for sale and illegal possession of hypodermic 
syringes. Gill's wife, Carol, 45, denied the same charges. 
</P>
<P>
The three, all of whom are bodybuilders, were arrested last month after an 
investigation by Whittier police, who said they found steroids and cocaine at 
the gym. Steroids and cocaine were also found at the Gills' home, and steroids 
and an AK-47 assault rifle were found at Weaver's home, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Gill and Weaver are free on $5,000 bail; Carol Gill is free on her own 
recognizance. All three defendants will have a preliminary hearing Aug. 29. 
</P>
<P>
The gym and the Gills' home were seized by federal and local authorities July 
12. Weaver's home was not seized. Federal marshals reopened the gym after the 
seizure and appointed an acting manager. 
</P>
</TEXT>
