<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECEPTION SLATED FOR DEPARTING COLLEGE PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COMPTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Farewell reception for Edison O. Jackson, president of Compton Community 
College, will be held Wednesday in the student lounge. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson is leaving Compton to become president in September of Medgar Evers 
College in Brooklyn, N.Y. The college is part of City University of New York. 
</P>
<P>
Educational and area civic leaders will participate in the farewell, which will 
begin with the reception at 6:30 p.m. and include a program at 8. Residents, 
college family and faculty may attend, according to Dean Warren A. Washington. 
</P>
<P>
The college Board of Trustees has named Washington interim president while a 
search is conducted to find a permanent replacement for Jackson. 
</P>
<P>
Public agencies and community organizations wishing to make presentations at 
the event may contact Washington at 637-2660. 
</P>
