6 ARRESTED IN GAMBLING RAID AT VIDEO ARCADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The owner of a Glendale video arcade and five other people were arrested on 
suspicion of gambling last week when officers discovered them playing blackjack 
in a locked back room of the business, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Raymond Hakoopian, 30, owner of Odyssey Video Arcade, was playing cards with 
friends in an office of the business at 213 S. Brand Blvd. when they were 
arrested about 5 p.m. Friday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Cards, a crap table and ledgers detailing debts of several hundred dollars were 
seized, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Odyssey Video Arcade is one of the largest arcades in Glendale and includes 
several billiard tables. 
</P>
<P>
Police said they have no evidence of gambling at other such establishments. 
</P>
<P>
Hakoopian declined to comment. 
</P>
<P>
Also arrested were Karapet Martirosyan, 27; Haytham Shamaoun, 26, and Varant 
Krikoian, 19, all of Glendale; George Livingston, 19, of North Hollywood, and 
Hamid Mahmoozi, 27, of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
All are scheduled to be arraigned in Glendale Municipal Court on Aug. 10. 
</P>
<P>
They face maximum sentences of six months in jail on the misdemeanor charges. 
</P>
