<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREPS TO CLASH IN ALL-STAR GRID CONTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 13th annual Los Angeles Prep Senior Bowl All-Star Football Classic will be 
played Saturday, July 22, at 7:30 p.m. at Santa Monica College Corsair Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Players from 40 Los Angeles area high schools will participate in the game,with 
the dividing line the Pasadena and Harbor Freeways. 
</P>
<P>
The game is sponsored by the Optimist Club of Santa Monica. Proceeds benefit 
the Optimist Boys Home in Northeast Los Angeles and community sports and 
recreation programs. 
</P>
<P>
Brad Ratcliff of University High is offensive head coach for South-West 
all-stars whose 38 man roster includes players from Hamilton, University, 
Venice, Westchester, Fairfax, Santa Monica, St. Monica, Daniel Murphy, Loyola , 
Culver City and St. Bernard. 
</P>
<P>
Among the top South-West mainstays are J. J. Johnson, Beverly Hills 
quarterback; Jerry Black, linebacker, John Zeigler, tackle, Steve Blinn, tight 
end and A. Dee Williams, defensive back, all from Santa Monica; Brian Townsley, 
wide receiver and Rynaldo Woodard, linebacker from University; Mike Wagner, 
running back and Mike Dunford, tight end, both of St. Monica; and Larry Avery, 
wide receiver and Vicent Bonner, defensive back, both of Westchester. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets are $7 for adults 18 and over; $5 for high school students with 
identification and $3 for children under 12. 
</P>
