<TEXT>
<P>
Steel Imports Rise: Although steel imports increased to 1.47 million tons in 
May, up 10% from April, they remained well below the level of a year earlier, 
according to an industry association. Imports for the first five months of the 
year were down dramatically, the American Iron &amp; Steel Institute said. 
Import tonnage for the first five months totaled 7.15 million tons, down 21% 
from January through May, 1988, the institute said. Foreign steel represented 
17.1% of the market in the first five months of this year, down from 20.7% in 
the 1988 period. The May tonnage represented 17.2% of the apparent supply in 
the U.S. market, compared to 16.4% in April and 21.5% in May, 1988. 
</P>
