<P>
Ameritech: The Chicago-based telecommunications company's second-quarter net 
income fell 9.8% from last year to $316.6 million. The 1988 quarter included a 
$42.1-million gain from the sale of its interest in Cantel, a Canadian cellular 
company. Excluding the gain, profit rose 2.3% in this year's second quarter. 
Revenue rose 3.1% to $2.6 billion, reflecting strong business volumes and 
increases in customer telephone lines and cellular operations. Ameritech is the 
parent of Bell companies serving Illinois, Indiana, Michigan, Ohio and 
Wisconsin, and other firms providing cellular communications, voice messaging, 
directories and lease financing. 
