</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Britain and Vietnam have agreed secretly to force thousands of Vietnamese 
refugees in Hong Kong to return home, British news reports said. The Guardian 
newspaper said the agreement was confirmed by unidentified government officials 
in London and in Hong Kong; however, neither the British Foreign Office nor 
Hong Kong authorities would comment. The newspaper said those to be repatriated 
have been classified as economic rather than political refugees and that more 
than half the 50,000 in Hong Kong are likely to be sent back home. It said 
repatriations may start in a week. The British Broadcasting Corp. said the 
agreement has been kept secret to avoid provoking unrest among refugees in the 
British colony. 
</P>
