<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. MARINE, 6 HONDURAN TROOPS HURT IN ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, Honduras 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One U.S. Marine and six Honduran troops were wounded when a grenade 
accidentally exploded during joint training near the southern Honduran town of 
San Lorenzo, a Honduran military official said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The five Hondurans were released and the U.S. Marine was in fair condition, 
U.S. military spokesman Maj. Donald Sensing said, but he withheld the names. A 
faulty grenade went off unexpectedly in the tube of a grenade launcher Tuesday 
injuring the operating crew. 
</P>
</TEXT>
