<P>
ATLANTIC SQUARE'S PLAN OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Responding to complaints from neighbors upset by plans to refurbish the 
Atlantic Square Shopping Center, the Planning Commission has unanimously 
approved changes in the proposed traffic patterns, loading areas and entrances 
to the center. 
</P>
<P>
The board also gave its approval for the conditional-use permit and the 
tenant-mix plan that the developer, Champion Development Co. of Long Beach, 
needs to build the $26 million project at the corner of South Atlantic 
Boulevard and Floral Drive. 
</P>
<P>
For nearly six hours, beginning on the night of July 13, the board heard 
testimony from about 20 residents, city officials and consultants. 
</P>
