<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Printronix Inc., an Irvine-based manufacturer of computer printers, reported a 
loss of $607,000 for its first quarter ended June 30, contrasted with net 
income of $1.4 million for the same period in 1988. Sales declined 18% to $29.3 
million from $35.5 million. The company said substantially lower European 
orders caused sales to drop. 
</P>
</TEXT>
