<HEADLINE>
<P>
MCDONNELL DOUGLAS IRVINE UNIT REPORTS PROFIT OF $18 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
McDonnell Douglas Information Systems Co., Irvine, reported earnings of $18 
million for the second quarter of 1989, contrasted with a loss of $22 million 
for the same period in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
The company said this is the first time that the company has made a profit in 
the second quarter or the first half in six years and credited the performance 
to increased sales and lower operating costs. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue declined 8%, to $278 million from $303 million. The company attributed 
the decrease to businesses the company no longer owns. The company last year 
reorganized its business units into four divisions. 
</P>
<P>
For the first half of 1989, McDonnell Douglas Information Systems earned $9 
million, up from a loss of $50 million in the first six months of 1988. Revenue 
dropped 6%, to $559 million from $594 million. 
</P>
<P>
McDonnell Douglas Information Systems, a division of McDonnell Douglas Corp., 
targets the networking, systems integration and computer systems markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
