<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
SENATE KILLS LIMITS ON PLO CONTACTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Senate today killed proposed legislation that would restrict U.S. contacts 
with the Palestine Liberation Organization after President Bush said it could 
destroy U.S. peace efforts in the Middle East. 
</P>
<P>
The measure, defeated by a vote of 75 to 23, would have banned U.S. 
negotiations with any PLO official who had prior knowledge of or participated 
in a terrorist attack that resulted in the death of any American. 
</P>
</TEXT>
