<P>
DC-10 FORCED DOWN IN CHICAGO BY A BIRD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A United Airlines DC-10 made an unscheduled landing today at O'Hare 
International Airport after a bird was sucked into an engine and the pilot shut 
it down. 
</P>
<P>
United Flight 23 from New York's J.F.K. Airport to San Francisco set down 
without incident at 9:58 a.m., said Mort Edelstein, a spokesman for the Federal 
Aviation Administration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
