SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
2 SPLIT $11-MILLION LOTTERY JACKPOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two lucky players picked all six numbers in the California Lottery's "Lotto 
6/49" game held Wednesday night and will split an $11.03 million jackpot, state 
lottery officials said today. The two winners will receive $5,515,173 each. 
</P>
<P>
Seven players picked five of six numbers plus the bonus number and won $233,275 
each, lottery officials said. A total of 369 people guessed five of six numbers 
and will take home $2,280 each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
