<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
AT&amp;T RINGS UP 18% RISE IN PROFITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co., the nation's largest telecommunications 
company, said today its profit in the second quarter rose 18% to $694 million. 
</P>
<P>
On a per share basis, the earnings increased to 66 cents a share from 55 cents. 
</P>
<P>
The communications giant said its revenues rose 5.2% to $9.26 billion from 
$8.80 billion a year ago. Expense controls allowed earnings to rise even faster 
than the revenues, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
Analysts said AT&amp;T's earnings were expected to rise due to strong demand 
for its long-distance telephone services. 
</P>
<P>
For the first half of the year the company had a net profit of $1.29 billion, 
compared with $1.09 billion a year ago. Revenues rose to $17.91 billion from 
$17.19 billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
