<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIGNON WIDENS HIS TOUR LEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
VILLARD-DE-LANS, France 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bicyclist Laurent Fignon of France extended his lead over Greg LeMond today 
with an individual victory in the 18th stage of the Tour de France. 
</P>
<P>
With three stages left, Fignon has a 50-second advantage over LeMond as he 
broke away again in the final stretch. 
</P>
<P>
Fignon, the 1983 and 1984 overall champion, won the leg from Bourg d'Oisans to 
Villard-de-Lans, near Grenoble, covering the 57 miles in 2 hours, 31 minutes, 
28 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Fignon added to his margin as LeMond, the 1986 winner, finished fifth in a 
group 24 seconds behind Fignon. 
</P>
<P>
Pedro Delgado of Spain, last year's champion, is still third but is 2:28 
behind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
